<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 08 at 2:25PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A moderate band of snow will impact portions of northwestern
Judith Basin and east central Cascade Counties through 300 PM MST...
At 223 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking moderate snow showers
along a line extending from 8 miles northwest of Geyser to 17 miles
south of Highwood to Belt. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Brief period of moderate snow.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Variable visibility down to a quarter mile or less and
slippery roads could result in hazardous driving conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Belt, Armington and Raynesford.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 200 between mile markers 0 and 15.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
